cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.MA, cs.AR 

The paper discusses the feasibility of multi-Gbps mm-wave cellular networks in an urban environment, which involves aspects of networking (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), millimeter-wave technology (cs.MM), machine learning and optimization (cs.MA), and augmented reality (cs.AR). However, the focus on networking and communication aspects makes cs.NI the most likely category, followed by cs.IT and cs.MM.
